5:
I knew that Mordiaga was a villain,
but not that he was a fool.
8:
Well, that explains why he's always
sneaking around.
11:
Please, please! You have to save my
master!
14:
As if I could say no to you, Gianini.
We'll help him.
27:
It's me, Gianini. I'm borrowing my
master's body for a moment.
31:
I see... With his soul trapped in that
mirror, Mordiaga's body is no more
than a vessel.
36:
Yeah, and one that's rotting fast! We
need to get his soul back sooner
rather than later!
44:
I'll use my master's body to connect
us to the dream world he's trapped
in.
46:
We can squeeze in there and
remind him he belongs with us!
54:
And here it is. I'd say this sword
hardly qualifies as "hidden" treasure.
57:
But the minister will be overjoyed to
see it. I expect he'll be quite
generous with his reward...
65:
A version from his younger days, I
imagine. Wait, what's that?
72:
A greater water sprite?! You must be
joking! This wasn't in the job
description!
78: Hey, we're here to help! Just hold on!
86:
*pant* That was no joke... I almost
kicked the bucket...
89:
It's always one thing or another with
you, huh...
92: Today's just not my day, that's all!
95:
Mortals... May your every breath be
cursed!
98:
Pfft, as if a curse'll scare me at this
point.
101:
(Grab that lamp at your feet and
get out of there!)
104: Huh? Did you guys say something?
107:
Wow, Mordiaga. That lamp at your
feet looks like it could be worth
some money.
111:
Good catch. A wanderer like me is
always in need of funds.
114: It's quite old. Might sell as an antique.
118:
The design looks familiar for some
reason... That's it! I found this lamp
when
133:
Isn't it obvious? Home, now that I
know where I belong.
150:
As much as it pains me to admit it, I
owe you my gratitude. Thanks.
There, gratitude given.
154:
Have you learned nothing from your
trials?
157:
That's Master for you. He's like a bad
habit I can't shake.
158:
Master, you do realize it's MY power
that's keeping your curse contained,
right? Some more sincere
appreciation wouldn't hurt.
161:
Less yapping and more moving,
Gianini. We're out of here.
165:
Wait, is THAT why Mordiaga's always
carrying the lamp?
170:
Hey, if you snooze around I'm
leaving you behind!
172:
It's treasure hunting time! I'll treat
you all to a drink after!
176:
It seems there is no curse in the
world that can cure him of his
character.
179:
Eh, stick by him, and maybe he'll
surprise us one day!
